ecember 3</li>\n<li>Setup days are November 30, December 1</li>\n</ul>\n			<a href=\"https://signup.com/client/invitation/6775657374/1884650/false#!1884650/false/false\" target=\"_self\" role=\"button\">\n							Choose Conference Task\n					</a>\n	<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">About Us</h4>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">LimmudBoston is a happening, a Jewish learningfest of culture and identity. From storytelling, music and meditation to Torah and Talmud, LimmudBoston offers inspiration and education – engaging beginners and scholars alike.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/who-we-are\">Learn more &gt;&gt;</a></p>\n	<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">Social Media</h4>\n	<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">Contact Us</h4>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><small><small><a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/about/contact-us\">Join our mailing list</a> to stay up to date and volunteer with LimmudBoston.</small></small></p>\n','Volunticipate!','','publish','closed','closed','','volunticipate','','','2017-06-03 17:55:32','2017-06-03 22:55:32','',0,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/?page_id=21',0,'page','',0),(22,3,'2017-05-25 16:44:03','2017-05-25 21:44:03','','Sharon and Rich Solomon','','inherit','open','closed','','sharon-and-rich-solomon','','','2017-05-25 16:44:03','2017-05-25 21:44:03','',21,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/wp/../sites/limmudboston/uploads/2017/05/Sharon-and-Rich-Solomon.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(24,3,'2017-05-25 16:47:22','2017-05-25 21:47:22','','Ken Hausman Videoing','','inherit','open','closed','','ken-hausman-videoing','','','2017-05-25 16:47:22','2017-05-25 21:47:22','',21,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/wp/../sites/limmudboston/uploads/2017/05/Ken-Hausman-Videoing.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(25,3,'2017-05-25 16:48:28','2017-05-25 21:48:28','Volunteer + Participate = Volunticipate!\r\n\r\nWe can\'t do this without you!\r\n\r\nVolunteering is a core value at Limmuds throughout the world. Presenter to name tag collector, setup to cleanup, Limmud participants pay to attend, and also volunteer in order to help support their local Limmud conference.  Please join a volunteer team, or choose a volunteer task, so that we can keep LimmudBoston affordable and accessible to all.\r\n\r\nTo join a planning team: (Link to SFDC)\r\n\r\nClick <a href=\"http://signup.com/go/gOkLgry\">HERE</a> to choose a task for LimmudBoston conference on Sunday, December 3, or on setup days (November 30, December 1).<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-22\" src=\"http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/uploads/2017/05/Sharon-and-Rich-Solomon-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-23\" src=\"http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/uploads/2017/05/Emma-Stitcher-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-24\" src=\"http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/uploads/2017/05/Ken-Hausman-Videoing.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"171\" height=\"256\" />','Volunticipate!','','inherit','closed','closed','','21-revision-v1','','','2017-05-25 16:48:28','2017-05-25 21:48:28','',21,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/21-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(26,3,'2017-05-25 16:49:01','2017-05-25 21:49:01','','Post #26','','trash','closed','closed','','__trashed','','','2017-05-26 12:04:04','2017-05-26 17:04:04','',0,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/?page_id=26',0,'page','',0),(27,3,'2017-05-25 16:49:01','2017-05-25 21:49:01','','Post #26','','inherit','closed','closed','','26-revision-v1','','','2017-05-25 16:49:01','2017-05-25 21:49:01','',26,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/26-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(28,3,'2017-05-25 19:14:31','2017-05-26 00:14:31','48in48: Please delete this page','LimmudBoston Conference','','publish','closed','closed','','limmudboston-conference','','','2017-05-30 18:23:32','2017-05-30 23:23:32','',0,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/?page_id=28',0,'page','',0),(29,3,'2017-05-25 19:14:31','2017-05-26 00:14:31','','LimmudBoston Conference','','inherit','closed','closed','','28-revision-v1','','','2017-05-25 19:14:31','2017-05-26 00:14:31','',28,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/28-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(30,3,'2017-05-25 19:15:02','2017-05-26 00:15:02','<h1>How to Propose a Session for LimmudBoston 2017</h1>\r\n<div class=\"post-entry\">\r\n<div id=\"attachment_1919\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\">\r\n\r\n<a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/chapel_presenting.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-0\" data-imagelightbox=\"0\"><img class=\"wp-image-1919 size-medium\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/chapel_presenting-200x300.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/chapel_presenting-200x300.jpg 200w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/chapel_presenting-100x150.jpg 100w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/chapel_presenting.jpg 533w\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n<h4 class=\"wp-caption-text\">© Meri Bond</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h4><strong>Register for LimmudBoston.</strong></h4>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h4><strong>Find Session Proposal Link in your confirmation email.\r\n</strong></h4>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h4>Submit completed session proposal.</h4>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe Program Team seeks creative, dynamic, enticing sessions.\r\n\r\nLike all Limmuds throughout the world, everyone attends as a learner. Presenters are also attendees. Register for LimmudBoston in order to receive the link to our Presenter Proposal Form. If your session is accepted, please plan on attending the conference for the day in addition to your session. The presenter form link comes with conference registration materials.\r\n\r\nWe welcome sessions on all Jewish topics, at many levels and in diverse media. Offer your passion: conventional or un-. Hands-on programs are especially welcome.\r\n\r\nMultiple submissions are welcome. Kindly complete one proposal form for each session submitted. The Program Team might choose only one, as we try to include as many presenters as possible.\r\n\r\nConsider, too, offering a session for Camp Limmud programs, ages 3-5, 6-8 or 9-13.\r\n\r\n<em>If event registration fee is a hardship, write to <a href=\"mailto:info@LimmudBoston.org\">info@LimmudBoston.org</a> to discuss a registration adjustment.\r\n</em>\r\n\r\nPresenters will be notified on a rolling basis, starting mid-August.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Conference registration may be found <a href=\"https://limmudboston2017.eventbrite.com\">HERE</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Authors/Performers/Artists: YES! You may sell your books/CDs/artwork at LimmudBoston. NO! You may not use your session just to sell your book. Sessions are your opportunity to teach, engage, entertain and inspire. Books may be sold in the lobby at the Authors\' Table. They may be sold outside of your classroom--but please keep hallways relatively quiet between sessions.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>\r\n\r\n</div>','Presenter Info','','publish','closed','closed','','presenter-info','','','2017-05-30 17:04:05','2017-05-30 22:04:05','',0,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/?page_id=30',0,'page','',0),(31,3,'2017-05-25 19:15:02','2017-05-26 00:15:02','','Presenter Info','','inherit','closed','closed','','30-revision-v1','','','2017-05-25 19:15:02','2017-05-26 00:15:02','',30,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/30-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(32,3,'2017-05-25 19:15:35','2017-05-26 00:15:35','<h2 class=\"shabbat supertitle\">Shabbat: The REST of Limmud</h2>\r\n<h1 class=\"shabbat title\">Engage a LimmudBoston Presenter for Shabbat (Dec. 1 &amp; 2)</h1>\r\n<div class=\"post-entry\">\r\n<h2 class=\"shabbat subtitle\"></h2>\r\n<div class=\"shabbat location\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"shabbat logistics\">\r\n\r\nCongregations, prayer communities, and havurot: <a href=\"mailto:info@LimmudBoston.org\">Contact us</a> to host a LimmudBoston presenter on the Shabbat prior to LimmudBoston’s Sunday conference, or create special Shabbat programming that is open to the LimmudBoston community.  Shabbat programming can be Friday evening, Saturday morning and/or Saturday evening (Havdalah).  <em>Please recognize that your congregation is responsible for any discussions of remuneration. </em>\r\n\r\n<em>Last year’s Shabbat presenters included: Rabbi Maurice Harris at <strong>Congregations Dorshei Tzedek in W. Newton</strong>; Rabbi Bill Hamilton of <strong>Brookline’s Kehillath Israel</strong>; Rabbi Dan Berman at <strong>Temple Reyim in Newton</strong>, and artist Mordechai Rosenstein at <strong>Temple Emunah in Lexington</strong>.</em>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"shabbat content\"><form action=\"https://www.salesforce.com/servlet/servlet.WebToLead?encoding=UTF-8\" method=\"POST\"><strong>YES! We want to host a Shabbat program before LimmudBoston 2017:</strong>\r\n\r\n48in48: This is a Salesforce.com Web-to-Lead Form:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nName of Congregation or Shabbat Community:<input id=\"company\" maxlength=\"40\" name=\"company\" size=\"20\" type=\"text\" />\r\n\r\n<label for=\"first_name\">Primary Contact First Name</label><input id=\"first_name\" maxlength=\"40\" name=\"first_name\" size=\"20\" type=\"text\" /> <label for=\"last_name\">Primary Contact Last Name</label><input id=\"last_name\" maxlength=\"80\" name=\"last_name\" size=\"20\" type=\"text\" />\r\n\r\n<label for=\"email\">Email</label><input id=\"email\" maxlength=\"80\" name=\"email\" size=\"20\" type=\"text\" />\r\n\r\n<label for=\"street\">Address</label><input id=\"street\" maxlength=\"80\" name=\"street\" size=\"20\" type=\"text\" /> <label for=\"city\">City</label><input id=\"city\" maxlength=\"40\" name=\"city\" size=\"20\" type=\"text\" /> <label for=\"state\">State/Province</label><input id=\"state\" maxlength=\"20\" name=\"state\" size=\"20\" type=\"text\" /> <label for=\"zip\">Zip</label><input id=\"zip\" maxlength=\"20\" name=\"zip\" size=\"20\" type=\"text\" />\r\n\r\n<label for=\"URL\">Website</label><input id=\"URL\" maxlength=\"80\" name=\"URL\" size=\"20\" type=\"text\" /> <label for=\"phone\">Phone</label><input id=\"phone\" maxlength=\"40\" name=\"phone\" size=\"20\" type=\"text\" /> <label for=\"mobile\">Mobile</label><input id=\"mobile\" maxlength=\"40\" name=\"mobile\" size=\"20\" type=\"text\" />\r\n\r\nDo you have arrangements already?\r\n\r\n</form></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<blockquote>Presenter Name: <input id=\"00NA000000AEzdy\" maxlength=\"100\" name=\"00NA000000AEzdy\" size=\"20\" type=\"text\" /> Date (mm/dd/yyyy): <input id=\"00NA000000AEze3\" name=\"00NA000000AEze3\" size=\"12\" type=\"text\" /></blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>Details to Publish: <textarea id=\"00NA000000AEze8\" name=\"00NA000000AEze8\" wrap=\"soft\"></textarea></blockquote>\r\n<div id=\"content_container\" class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"eight columns\">\r\n<div id=\"middle-col\">\r\n<div class=\"post-entry\">\r\n<div class=\"shabbat content\"><form action=\"https://www.salesforce.com/servlet/servlet.WebToLead?encoding=UTF-8\" method=\"POST\">\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/candles_etc.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-294 size-full\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/candles_etc.jpg\" alt=\"Candles for Shabbat\" width=\"259\" height=\"194\" /></a></h3>\r\n</form></div>\r\n<div class=\"shabbat speaker-pic\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"shabbat speaker-bio\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"shabbat other\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"shabbat map three columns\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"four columns\">\r\n<div id=\"sidebar\">\r\n<div id=\"nav_menu-10\" class=\"widget-container-primary widget_nav_menu\">\r\n<h3 class=\"widget-title\">Shabbat Links</h3>\r\n<div class=\"menu-shabbat-general-menu-container\">\r\n<ul id=\"menu-shabbat-general-menu\" class=\"menu\">\r\n 	<li id=\"menu-item-2040\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-2040\"><a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/shabbat-hosting/\">Hosting a Shabbat Experience</a></li>\r\n 	<li id=\"menu-item-2167\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-2167\"><a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2015/shabbat-2015/\">Shabbat Programs 2015</a></li>\r\n 	<li id=\"menu-item-2041\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-2041\"><a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2014/shabbat-2014/\">Shabbat Programs 2014</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Shabbat: the REST of Limmud','','publish','closed','closed','','shabbat-the-rest-of-limmud','','','2017-05-26 12:18:20','2017-05-26 17:18:20','',0,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/?page_id=32',0,'page','',0),(33,3,'2017-05-25 19:15:35','2017-05-26 00:15:35','','Shabbat: the REST of Limmud','','inherit','closed','closed','','32-revision-v1','','','2017-05-25 19:15:35','2017-05-26 00:15:35','',32,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/32-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(34,3,'2017-05-25 19:15:56','2017-05-26 00:15:56','\n	<h1>48in48: Please do not publish this page yet.</h1>\n<a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2017/\">Conference 2017</a>\n<h1>Camp Limmud</h1>\n<p><img src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/kids_painting_2-300x200.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/kids_painting_2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/kids_painting_2-150x100.jpg 150w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/kids_painting_2.jpg 800w\" alt=\"Kids painting at Camp Limmud 2014\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></p>\n<p>Kids painting at Camp Limmud 2014<br />\nPhoto credit: Meri Bond</p>\n<p><a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/JCCGB-logo.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-0\" data-imagelightbox=\"0\"><img src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/JCCGB-logo-150x57.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/JCCGB-logo-150x57.jpg 150w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/JCCGB-logo-300x114.jpg 300w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/JCCGB-logo.jpg 367w\" alt=\"jccgb-logo\" width=\"150\" height=\"57\" /></a></p>\n<p>LimmudBoston offers an affordable, fun and innovative Camp Limmud program for children from ages 3-13.</p>\n<p>Parents must be registered for LimmudBoston in order to register their child for Camp Limmud. Camp Limmud costs $25 per child and is held during the same hours as the conference. Register both parents and children <a href=\"http://lb2016.eventbrite.com\">here.</a></p>\n<p>To help plan Camp Limmud, volunteer at <a title=\"Volunteer at Camp Limmud\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2014/camp-limmud/volunteer-at-camp-limmud/\">this page.</a></p>\n<p>Camp Limmud is run by staff from the Early Learning Center of the JCC of Greater Boston.</p>\n<h2>More Information</h2>\n<p>Jump to a section:<br />\n<a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2017/camp-limmud/#Cost\">Cost</a> / <a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2017/camp-limmud/#Ages\">Ages</a> / <a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2017/camp-limmud/#Program\">Program</a> / <a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2017/camp-limmud/#Staff\">Staff</a> / <a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2017/camp-limmud/#SpecialNeeds\">Special Needs</a> / <a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2017/camp-limmud/#ParentsAndChildren\">Parents and Children Together </a>/ <a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2017/camp-limmud/#HelpPlan\">Help Plan</a> / <a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2014/teens-at-limmudboston/\">Teens</a></p>\n<h3>Cost</h3>\n<p><a id=\"Cost\"></a>Thanks to a Combined Jewish Philanthropies (CJP) Innovation Grant, the all-day Camp Limmud program cost is only $25 per child.</p>\n<p>Camp Limmud parents for whom the cost of their own conference registration poses a financial hardship should get in touch with us at <a href=\"mailto:info@limmudboston.org\">info@limmudboston.org</a>.</p>\n<h3>Ages</h3>\n<p><a id=\"Ages\"></a>Camp Limmud has 3 age groupings:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>ages 3-5</li>\n<li>ages 6-8</li>\n<li>ages 9-13</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Program</h3>\n<p><a id=\"Program\"></a>All three children’s programs will feature a variety of activities. Experienced preschool educators and counselors stay with the children throughout the day as top Jewish educators, musicians, and artists present creative, exciting, and educational sessions.<br />\n<a title=\"Camp Limmud Programming\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2014/camp-limmud/camp-limmud-programming/\">More information…</a></p>\n<h3>Staff</h3>\n<p><a id=\"Staff\"></a>Our Camp Limmud staff is composed of adults college-age or older who have experience planning and implementing children’s educational and/or leadership programs in a variety of communities (i.e. former camp counselors, Jewish Educators, religious school teachers, day care providers, etc.).</p>\n<p>Assistant counselors will include high school students (11th and 12th graders) who are interested in helping support Camp Limmud programming.</p>\n<p>Camp Limmud staff positions are PAID positions. If you are interested in working at Camp Limmud during the conference contact Terri Swartz Russell, LB co-chair, at <a href=\"mailto:terrisrussell@yahoo.com\">terrisrussell@yahoo.com</a> or 617-448-3996.</p>\n<h3>Special Needs</h3>\n<p><a id=\"SpecialNeeds\"></a>LimmudBoston is partnering with Greater Boston Yachad/The National Jewish Council for Disabilities in order to extend an invitation to families with children who have special needs to attend our conference. Special needs students will be accompanied by 1:1 teen volunteers from the Yachad clubs at Maimonides, Gann Academy and The Binah School.</p>\n<p>If your child has special needs please contact Liz Offen, Director, Greater Boston &amp; New England Yachad. Liz may be reached at <a href=\"mailto:bostonyachad@ou.org\">bostonyachad@ou.org</a> or 617-285-0007.</p>\n<h3>Parents and Children Together</h3>\n<p><a id=\"ParentsAndChildren\"></a>A selection of sessions are geared specifically for Parents and Children to participate in together throughout the conference day. Parents will receive a copy of the full Camp Limmud program and may join their child/ren in the Camp Limmud area for these special sessions if they wish.</p>\n<h3>Help Plan Camp Limmud</h3>\n<p><a id=\"HelpPlan\"></a>We are now planning the children’s program for LimmudBoston.</p>\n<p>If you are interested in helping plan our Camp Limmud children’s programs please contact Terri Swartz Russell, LB co-chair, at <a href=\"mailto:terrisrussell@yahoo.com\">terrisrussell@yahoo.com</a> or 617-448-3996.</p>\n<p>To learn more about volunteering at Camp Limmud, <a title=\"Volunteer at Camp Limmud\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2014/camp-limmud/volunteer-at-camp-limmud/\">click here</a>.</p>\n<h3>Teens at Limmud</h3>\n<p><a id=\"Teens\"></a>Please see <a title=\"Teens at LimmudBoston\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2014/teens-at-limmudboston/\">this page</a>.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>This program is supported in part by the CJP Innovation Grants Committee.</p>\n','Camp Limmud','','publish','closed','closed','','camp-limmud','','','2017-06-02 23:57:40','2017-06-03 04:57:40','',0,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/?page_id=34',0,'page','',0),(35,3,'2017-05-25 19:15:56','2017-05-26 00:15:56','','Camp Limmud','','inherit','closed','closed','','34-revision-v1','','','2017-05-25 19:15:56','2017-05-26 00:15:56','',34,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/34-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(36,3,'2017-05-25 19:16:32','2017-05-26 00:16:32','<div id=\"content_container\" class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"nine columns\">\r\n<div id=\"right-col\">\r\n<div class=\"crumbs\"><a class=\"crumb\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2017/\">Conference 2017</a></div>\r\n<h1>CJP Educators</h1>\r\n<div class=\"post-entry\">\r\n<div id=\"attachment_1793\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\">\r\n\r\n<a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Pink_sweater1.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-0\" data-imagelightbox=\"0\"><img class=\"wp-image-1793 \" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Pink_sweater1-200x300.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 176px) 100vw, 176px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Pink_sweater1-200x300.jpg 200w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Pink_sweater1-100x150.jpg 100w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Pink_sweater1.jpg 533w\" alt=\"Young educator presenting at LimmudBoston 2014\" width=\"176\" height=\"264\" /></a>\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\">© Meri Bond</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nCJP subsidizes local educators who come to LimmudBoston for special day of learning. By supporting educators, we hope to strengthen the broader education community, creating a positive impact on the experiences of all learners in our schools.\r\n\r\nThroughout the day there are special sessions geared toward educators and fostering conversations in the community new ideas for:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Supplementary school models</li>\r\n 	<li>Pedagogies</li>\r\n 	<li>Realities in learners’ lives</li>\r\n 	<li>Ways to meet learners’ special needs</li>\r\n 	<li>Education technologies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nLimmudBoston offers many ways for educators to share ideas.\r\n\r\nLimmudBoston celebrates lifelong Jewish learning, for beginners to scholars, young to young-at-heart. Thus please remember to promote LimmudBoston in your school communities. Add a link to the LimmudBoston website (www.limmudboston.org) to your school website and to the website of your congregation.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://limmudboston2017.eventbrite.com\">Register for the conference</a> in order to offer a session for LimmudBoston educators.\r\n\r\n<em>This program is supported in part by Combined Jewish Philanthropies of Greater Boston.</em>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Supported-by-CJP.png\" data-rel=\"lightbox-1\" data-imagelightbox=\"1\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-190\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Supported-by-CJP.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Supported-by-CJP.png 199w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Supported-by-CJP-150x73.png 150w\" alt=\"Supported-by-CJP\" width=\"199\" height=\"98\" /></a>\r\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"one column\"></div>\r\n</div>','CJP Educators','','publish','closed','closed','','cjp-educators','','','2017-05-30 06:54:41','2017-05-30 11:54:41','',0,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/?page_id=36',0,'page','',0),(37,3,'2017-05-25 19:16:32','2017-05-26 00:16:32','','CJP Educators','','inherit','closed','closed','','36-revision-v1','','','2017-05-25 19:16:32','2017-05-26 00:16:32','',36,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/36-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(38,3,'2017-05-25 19:16:54','2017-05-26 00:16:54','\n	<h1 id=\"header_container\"><strong>Make a Donation</strong></h1>\n<p>Please click on this Donate button:</p>\n<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\" target=\"_top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><input name=\"cmd\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"_s-xclick\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><input name=\"hosted_button_id\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"4WRJT6HPADCU8\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><input alt=\"PayPal - The safer, easier way to pay online!\" name=\"submit\" src=\"http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/uploads/2017/05/paypal.jpg\" type=\"image\" /></p>\n</form>\n<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\" target=\"_top\"><img src=\"http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/uploads/2017/05/paypal.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"169\" /></p>\n</form>\n<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\" target=\"_top\">Your LimmudBoston donation helps us continue the work which inspires and unites New England’s many Jewish communities, and helps us continue the core practice of Limmud International, that all who wish to learn can be included, regardless of financial circumstances.</p>\n<p>LimmudBoston, Inc. is a 501(c)3 tax exempt organization. Contributions are tax deductible to the extent allowed by law as long as LimmudBoston, Inc. provided no goods or services in exchange for your contribution.</p>\n<p>Donations received before November 15 will be acknowledged in the annual LimmudBoston conference program book given to every conference attendee.</p>\n<p>Please consider the following amounts, or choose an amount that fits your wallet:</p>\n<p><strong>Pillars of Learning</strong>, $500 or more, helps to fund a presenter; receives 4 admissions;</p>\n<p><strong>Prophets</strong>, $360-499, receive conference admission for four;</p>\n<p><strong>Scholars</strong>, $180-359, receive conference admission for two;</p>\n<p><strong>Learners</strong>, $118-179, receive conference admission for one;</p>\n<p><strong>Well-Wishers</strong>, $72 &amp; above, will be listed in the LimmudBoston Program Book.</p>\n</form>\n<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\" target=\"_top\"></form>\n<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\" target=\"_top\">If you prefer, you can send a check by mail. Please make your check payable to LimmudBoston with “LimmudBoston” in the memo line, and send it to:</p>\n<p>LimmudBoston<br />\nPO Box 36<br />\nWaban MA 02468</p>\n<p>Notes</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Your contribution will be noted in the LimmudBoston Program Book.</li>\n<li>Please indicate if you wish to remain anonymous.</li>\n<li>If you wish to make a donation in honor of, or in memory of, one or more people, please indicate this and the information will be included.</li>\n<li>Sponsorship opportunities are available. For details contact LimmudBoston  <a href=\"mailto:info@LimmudBoston.org\">info@LimmudBoston.org </a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</form>\n	<h3>Become a Friend of LimmudBoston</h3>\n<p>A wonderful way to support our work is to become a Friend of LimmudBoston. <a href=\"https://www.limmudboston.org/support/become-a-friend/\">Find out more here</a>.</p>\n<h3>Thank You Friends and Supporters!</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/support/silent-auction/support/friends-of-limmudboston-2016/\"> 2016 Friends of LimmudBoston</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/support/silent-auction/support/2015-friends-of-limmudboston\">2015 Friends of LimmudBoston</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/support/silent-auction/support/2014-friends-of-limmudboston\">2014 Friends of LimmudBoston</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/support/silent-auction/support/supporters\">Friends and Supporters from previous years</a></p>\n','Make a Donation','','publish','closed','closed','','make-a-donation','','','2017-06-03 19:04:42','2017-06-04 00:04:42','',0,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/?page_id=38',0,'page','',0),(39,3,'2017-05-25 19:16:54','2017-05-26 00:16:54','','Make a Donation','','inherit','closed','closed','','38-revision-v1','','','2017-05-25 19:16:54','2017-05-26 00:16:54','',38,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/38-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(40,3,'2017-05-25 19:17:21','2017-05-26 00:17:21','\n	<h1>Friends of LimmudBoston 2016</h1>\n<p><strong><em>Thank you to all the Friends and Supporters of LimmudBoston 2016! Without