en\" data-mce-fragment=\"1\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nAaron Seidman 2\r\n\r\n</div>','Chai Alive! Videos','','inherit','closed','closed','','105-revision-v1','','','2017-05-26 12:49:28','2017-05-26 17:49:28','',105,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/105-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(108,3,'2017-05-26 12:50:10','2017-05-26 17:50:10','','Chai Alive! Videostrash','','inherit','closed','closed','','59-revision-v1','','','2017-05-26 12:50:10','2017-05-26 17:50:10','',59,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/59-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(109,3,'2017-05-26 12:51:50','2017-05-26 17:51:50','\n	<h1>About Us</h1>\n<h2>What is LimmudBoston?</h2>\n<h2>Everyone is a Learner at LimmudBoston!</h2>\n<p><a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Raising_hand1.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-0\" data-imagelightbox=\"0\"><img src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Raising_hand1-300x200.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Raising_hand1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Raising_hand1-150x100.jpg 150w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Raising_hand1.jpg 800w\" alt=\"Audience member raising her hand\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a>©Meri Bond</p>\n<p><strong>Everyone is a learner!</strong> LimmudBoston is the annual, volunteer-driven Jewish learning festival of culture and identity which includes everything from food demos and performance to panel discussions and individual talks. Learn! Listen! Watch! Wonder!  LimmudBoston workshops explore life cycle events, Israel, spirituality and identity. At LimmudBoston, we learn and move and explore Jewish topics. Each conference offers nearly 100 learning presentations and hands-on sessions on Torah, text, Jewish identity, movement, meditation, music, food, life cycle, theory and practice—and more.</p>\n<p><a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Age-diversity.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-1\" data-imagelightbox=\"1\"><img src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Age-diversity-300x200.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Age-diversity-300x200.jpg 300w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Age-diversity-150x100.jpg 150w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Age-diversity.jpg 800w\" alt=\"Two volunticipants: an old woman and a young man\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a>©Meri Bond</p>\n<p><strong>Anyone may offer to present a session! </strong>Just like the 80+ Limmud conferences held around the world, the LimmudBoston program team reviews session proposals from anyone with a passion to present a Jewish topic. Presenters also attend LimmudBoston as learners.</p>\n<p><strong>Volunteers make LimmudBoston! </strong>Nearly everyone pitches in by both paying to attend the conference, and or volunteering to help with a planning team, or by choosing a task on conference day.</p>\n<h4><em>No matter where you are on the spectrum of Jewish living, there is more to learn and more to do. As we learn from Pirke Avot, “Turn it and turn it for everything is in it, and through it you will perceive clearly.”</em> — Pirkei Avot, Chapters of the Sages. 5:26</h4>\n<h2>Shabbat: The REST of LimmudBoston</h2>\n<p>The entire community can be a weekend of learning when area congregations engage LimmudBoston presenters for Shabbat. We will list your congregation as a LimmudBoston Shabbat opportunity if your congregation:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your congregation wants to hire one of the LimmudBoston presenters coming for our Sunday conference; or</li>\n<li>Your Congregation already has a Shabbat speaker who will inspire Jewish learning\n<ul>\n<li><a title=\"Shabbat: The REST of Limmud\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/shabbat/\">LimmudBoston Shabbat experience programs</a> in area synagogues. LimmudBoston presenters serve as visiting scholars throughout the area. Learn more on our Shabbat Experience page.  Your Shabbat community can be one of a select group of Boston area synagogues to host a special Shabbat learning opportunity in conjunction with our upcoming LimmudBoston conference.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Everyone is welcome at LimmudBoston</h2>\n<p>LimmudBoston offers lots of points of view. LimmudBoston events are for beginners and scholars; the young and the young-at-heart. The Limmud flavor includes diversity of presenters, topics, style, age, participation, gender participation and traditions.</p>\n<p>For more information on attending as a teenager, see <a title=\"Teens at LimmudBoston\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2014/teens-at-limmudboston/\">this page</a>.</p>\n<h2>Camp Limmud</h2>\n<p><a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kids_from_back.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-2\" data-imagelightbox=\"2\"><img src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kids_from_back-200x300.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kids_from_back-200x300.jpg 200w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kids_from_back-100x150.jpg 100w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kids_from_back.jpg 533w\" alt=\"Kids gathered around a table\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<p>©2014 Meri Bond</p>\n<p>The <a title=\"Camp Limmud\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2014/camp-limmud/\">Camp Limmud program </a>offers child care and programming for children ages 3-14. Presenters from LimmudBoston have also presented for the Camp Limmud kids. Camp Limmud participation is by reservation only.</p>\n<h3>Want to know more?</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a title=\"Testimonials\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/about/testimonials/\">Testimonials</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Values and Principles of Limmud International\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/about/values-and-principles-of-limmud-international/\">Values and Principles</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"LimmudBoston in the News\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/about/limmudboston-in-the-news/\">LimmudBoston in the News</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/about/who-we-are/\">Our Board</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Ready to get involved?</h3>\n<p><a title=\"Volunticipate\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/volunticipate/\">Click here to volunteer</a> or send an email to: <a href=\"mailto:info@limmudboston.org\">info@Limmudboston.org</a></p>\n','About Us','','publish','closed','closed','','about-us','','','2017-06-02 23:34:21','2017-06-03 04:34:21','',0,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/?page_id=109',0,'page','',0),(110,3,'2017-05-26 12:51:50','2017-05-26 17:51:50','<h1>About Us</h1>\r\n<div class=\"post-entry\">\r\n<h2>What is LimmudBoston?</h2>\r\n<div id=\"attachment_1799\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Raising_hand1.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-0\" data-imagelightbox=\"0\"><img class=\"wp-image-1799 size-medium\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Raising_hand1-300x200.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Raising_hand1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Raising_hand1-150x100.jpg 150w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Raising_hand1.jpg 800w\" alt=\"Audience member raising her hand\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a>\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\">©2014 Meri Bond</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nLimmudBoston is more than just an all-day conference of Jewish learning.  It’s a happening, a Jewish learningfest of culture and identity. From storytelling, music and meditation to Torah and Talmud, LimmudBoston offers inspiration and education – engaging beginners and scholars alike. Discuss, listen, watch and wonder–in workshops that explore lifecycle, Israel, spirituality and identity. Dance and clap; sing and shop; bake and taste!\r\n<div id=\"attachment_1716\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\"><a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Age-diversity.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-1\" data-imagelightbox=\"1\"><img class=\"wp-image-1716 size-medium\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Age-diversity-300x200.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Age-diversity-300x200.jpg 300w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Age-diversity-150x100.jpg 150w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Age-diversity.jpg 800w\" alt=\"Two volunticipants: an old woman and a young man\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a>\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\">©2014 Meri Bond</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNo matter where you are on the spectrum of Jewish living, there is more to learn and more to do. As we learn from Pirke Avot, “Turn it and turn it for everything is in it, and through it you will perceive clearly.” — Pirkei Avot, Chapters of the Sages. 5:26\r\n\r\nLimmudBoston is an innovative, volunteer-driven celebration of Jewish lifelong learning for the entire community, beginner to scholar and young to young-at-heart. We present the best in Jewish scholarship, arts, music and community opportunities.\r\n\r\nOne of 60+ Limmud conferences worldwide that model the very successful Limmud UK, LimmudBoston recognizes that everyone is a learner—and everyone can be a presenter. LimmudBoston offers over 100 learning presentations and hands-on sessions covering Torah text, Jewish identity, movement, meditation, music, food, lifecycle, theory and practice—and more.\r\n<h2>Camp Limmud</h2>\r\n<div id=\"attachment_1915\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kids_from_back.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-2\" data-imagelightbox=\"2\"><img class=\"wp-image-1915 size-medium\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kids_from_back-200x300.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kids_from_back-200x300.jpg 200w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kids_from_back-100x150.jpg 100w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kids_from_back.jpg 533w\" alt=\"Kids gathered around a table\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\">©2014 Meri Bond</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nThe <a title=\"Camp Limmud\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2014/camp-limmud/\">Camp Limmud program </a>offers child care and programming for children ages 3-14. Presenters from LimmudBoston have also presented for the Camp Limmud kids. Camp Limmud participation is by reservation only.\r\n<h2>The LimmudBoston Shabbat Experience</h2>\r\nGet a jump on LimmudBoston with one of the exciting <a title=\"Shabbat: The REST of Limmud\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/shabbat/\">LimmudBoston Shabbat experience programs</a> in area synagogues. LimmudBoston presenters serve as visiting scholars throughout the area. Learn more on our Shabbat Experience page.  Your Shabbat community can be one of a select group of Boston area synagogues to host a special Shabbat learning opportunity in conjunction with our upcoming LimmudBoston conference.\r\n<h2>Everyone is welcome at LimmudBoston</h2>\r\nLimmudBoston offers lots of points of view. LimmudBoston events are for beginners and scholars; the young and the young-at-heart. The Limmud flavor includes diversity of presenters, topics, style, age, participation, gender participation and traditions.\r\n\r\nFor more information on attending as a teenager, see <a title=\"Teens at LimmudBoston\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2014/teens-at-limmudboston/\">this page</a>.\r\n<h3>Want to know more?</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"noBullets\">\r\n 	<li><a title=\"Testimonials\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/about/testimonials/\">Testimonials</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a title=\"Values and Principles of Limmud International\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/about/values-and-principles-of-limmud-international/\">Values and Principles</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a title=\"LimmudBoston in the News\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/about/limmudboston-in-the-news/\">LimmudBoston in the News</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/about/who-we-are/\">Our Board</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Ready to get involved?</h3>\r\n<a title=\"Volunticipate\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/volunticipate/\">Click here to volunteer</a> or send an email to: <a href=\"mailto:info@limmudboston.org\">info@Limmudboston.org</a>\r\n\r\n</div>','About Us','','inherit','closed','closed','','109-revision-v1','','','2017-05-26 12:51:50','2017-05-26 17:51:50','',109,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/109-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(111,3,'2017-05-26 12:52:40','2017-05-26 17:52:40','<h1>Contact Us</h1>\r\n<div class=\"post-entry\">\r\n<div class=\"clear\">\r\n\r\n<a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/contactUs1.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-0\" data-imagelightbox=\"0\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-172\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/contactUs1.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 250px) 100vw, 250px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/contactUs1.jpg 250w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/contactUs1-150x112.jpg 150w\" alt=\"contactUs1\" width=\"250\" height=\"188\" /></a>\r\n\r\nLimmudBoston is almost completely run by volunteers.\r\n\r\nSend general questions to: <a href=\"mailto:info@limmudboston.org\">info@LimmudBoston.org</a>\r\n\r\nSnail mail may be addressed to:\r\nPO Box 36, Waban, MA 02468\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>To keep up with the latest in LimmudBoston news, please join the mailing list.</h3>\r\n<form action=\"https://www.salesforce.com/servlet/servlet.WebToLead?encoding=UTF-8\" method=\