0\" name=\"zip\" size=\"20\" type=\"text\" />\r\n\r\n<label for=\"country\">Country\r\n</label> <input id=\"country\" maxlength=\"40\" name=\"country\" size=\"20\" type=\"text\" />\r\n\r\n</form></div>\r\n<div id=\"content_container\" class=\"row\"></div>','Contact','','inherit','closed','closed','','51-revision-v1','','','2017-05-26 12:53:18','2017-05-26 17:53:18','',51,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/51-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(113,3,'2017-05-26 12:53:41','2017-05-26 17:53:41','<h1>Who We Are</h1>\r\n<div class=\"post-entry\">\r\n<div id=\"attachment_2972\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/2016-12-04-LimmudBoston-Board.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-0\" data-imagelightbox=\"0\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-2972\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/2016-12-04-LimmudBoston-Board-150x116.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/2016-12-04-LimmudBoston-Board-150x116.jpg 150w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/2016-12-04-LimmudBoston-Board-300x232.jpg 300w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/2016-12-04-LimmudBoston-Board-768x593.jpg 768w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/2016-12-04-LimmudBoston-Board-1024x791.jpg 1024w\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"116\" /></a>\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Board: Eric Karp, Alan Teperow (Chair), Terri Swartz Russell, Sean Wald, Marcia Plumb, Emma Stitcher, Steffi Aronson Karp, Wendy Liebow, Julie Wolkoff, Naomi Gurt Lind <em>Photo: Meri Bond</em></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLimmudBoston is a volunteer-driven, independent, pan-denominational organization dedicated to the creation of engaging opportunities to experience and celebrate Jewish learning and culture.\r\n\r\nVolunteer + Participate = <a title=\"Volunticipate\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/volunticipate/\">Volunticipate</a>! <a title=\"Volunticipate\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/volunticipate/\">Click here to join a team now</a>.\r\n\r\nLike Limmud conferences everywhere, LimmudBoston runs on volunteer power. Our volunteer teams include:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Program  Shabbat; Chavruta; Site &amp; Signage; Volunteer Coordination; Program Book; Music &amp; Performance; PR &amp; Outreach; Food; Technology</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nLimmudBoston is part of Limmud International, and represents one of more than 80 independent worldwide Limmud conferences. We follow <a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/about/values-and-principles-of-limmud-international/\">Limmud International Values &amp; Principles</a>.\r\n<h2>Who We Are</h2>\r\n<div class=\"clear\">\r\n<h3><a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Steffi-e1430062700303.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-1\" data-imagelightbox=\"1\"><img class=\"clear wp-image-2030 size-thumbnail alignleft\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Steffi-e1430062700303-130x150.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 130px) 100vw, 130px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Steffi-e1430062700303-130x150.jpg 130w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Steffi-e1430062700303-261x300.jpg 261w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Steffi-e1430062700303.jpg 482w\" alt=\"Steffi Aronson Karp\" width=\"130\" height=\"150\" /></a>Steffi Aronson Karp, President</h3>\r\nLimmudBoston is run from the home of Steffi Aronson Karp, founder of LimmudBoston, who has been a Jewish conference junkie since her high school days in NEFTY, NFTY and SMARTY on Boston’s North Shore. In 2008, after attending her first Limmud in Atlanta, GA, she began creating LimmudBoston.  Steffi has participated in Limmud conferences in the UK, Philadelphia, New York and Baltimore, Miami, New Orleans and Toronto. In 2013, Steffi received the Klal Yisrael Award from the Synagogue Council of Massachusetts, as recognition for uniting area Jewish communities through LimmudBoston.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clear\">\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-41 size-thumbnail\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/concert_steffi_terri-e1430062072891-101x150.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 101px) 100vw, 101px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/concert_steffi_terri-e1430062072891-101x150.jpg 101w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/concert_steffi_terri-e1430062072891-202x300.jpg 202w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/concert_steffi_terri-e1430062072891-688x1024.jpg 688w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/concert_steffi_terri-e1430062072891.jpg 712w\" alt=\"Terri Swartz Russell\" width=\"101\" height=\"150\" />Terri Swartz Russell, LimmudBoston Board</h3>\r\nTerri Swartz Russell is the Family Educator at Temple Emanuel in Newton. She is an active member of Temple Emunah, Lexington, where she serves as co-chair of its Adult Education committee. Terri was the first to volunteer for LimmudBoston, was co-chair of the conference from 2011-2013, and currently serves as the Chair of the LimmudBoston Board.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clear\">\r\n<h3><img class=\"clear alignleft wp-image-1657 size-thumbnail\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/standing_in_lobby-e1430061616439-125x150.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 125px) 100vw, 125px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/standing_in_lobby-e1430061616439-125x150.jpg 125w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/standing_in_lobby-e1430061616439-251x300.jpg 251w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/standing_in_lobby-e1430061616439.jpg 254w\" alt=\"Jeri Robins\" width=\"125\" height=\"150\" />Jeri Robins, Music Team Leader</h3>\r\nCantor Robins has led the Music Team for LimmudBoston for several years. She currently serves Temple Beth Shalom of the North Shore in Peabody, Massachusetts in the dual role of Cantor and Director of Education.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clear\">\r\n<h3>Julie Wolkoff, Vice Chair<img class=\"clear alignleft wp-image-1600 size-thumbnail\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Volunteering-signs-e1430061422869-137x150.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 137px) 100vw, 137px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Volunteering-signs-e1430061422869-137x150.jpg 137w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Volunteering-signs-e1430061422869-273x300.jpg 273w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Volunteering-signs-e1430061422869.jpg 338w\" alt=\"Julie Wolkoff\" width=\"137\" height=\"150\" /></h3>\r\nRabbi Julie Wolkoff, D.Min. was ordained from HUC-JIR in 1982. She received her Doctor of Ministry degree from HUC-JIR in 1996. She is a chaplain with Care Alternatives Hospice in Marlborough, MA.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h3>Wendy Liebow</h3>\r\nWendy Liebow has many years of program experience at Temple Isaiah in Lexington, where she served two terms as VP of Programming and many more co-chairing various committees.    She lives in Lexington with her husband, Scott Burson.\r\n<h3>Barbara Posnick</h3>\r\nBarbara Posnick, of Wayland, served as Program Book editor for LimmudBoston 2012.  This year she is working with Wendy Liebow as Co-Chair of the Program Team.\r\n<h3>Barbara Miller</h3>\r\nBarbara Miller wrote to LimmudBoston in 2009 to say that she’s “in.” Put her to work. And we’ve done just that. Barbara has led the Site Team, working closely with every group in order to make sure that the building fits the needs of LimmudBoston.\r\n<h3>EJ Cohen-Music Team</h3>\r\nEJ Cohen brings years of experience with Limmud UK to the new world version, LimmudBoston.  She has spent 30+ years combining expertise from the worlds of Deaf and Jewish education.\r\n<h3>Maureen Mintz-Food Team</h3>\r\nMaureen Mintz  It wouldn’t be a Jewish conference without food, and lots of it. Maureen Mintz and her Food Team communicate with our kosher caterers, to bring yummy lunch to LimmudBoston participants. The food team also arranges for lots of snacks throughout the conference day.\r\n<h3>Emma Stitcher-Signage Queen</h3>\r\nLimmudBoston is lucky to have Emma Stitcher, our Signage expert. Emma and her family attended many Limmuds when they lived in the UK. In fact, the Stitcher daughters celebrated their b’not mitvah at Limmud. Emma also serves as our best on-site advisor for WWLD–What would Limmud do?!\r\n<div id=\"attachment_202\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/whoWeAre_steffiTerri.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-2\" data-imagelightbox=\"2\"><img class=\" wp-image-202\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/whoWeAre_steffiTerri.jpg\" alt=\"Steffi Aronson Karp and Terri Swartz Russell\" width=\"170\" height=\"113\" /></a>\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Steffi Aronson Karp and Terri Swartz Russell</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"attachment_201\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/whoWeAre_2012Team.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-3\" data-imagelightbox=\"3\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-201\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/whoWeAre_2012Team.jpg\" alt=\" Terri Swartz Russell with LimmudBoston 2012 Program Team leaders, Barbara Posnick (left) and Wendy Liebow (right)\" width=\"150\" height=\"113\" /></a>\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Terri Swartz Russell with LimmudBoston 2012 Program Team leaders, Barbara Posnick (left) and Wendy Liebow (right)</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"attachment_200\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/whoWeAre_2011Team.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-4\" data-imagelightbox=\"4\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-200\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/whoWeAre_2011Team.jpg\" alt=\"LimmudBoston 2011 Planners, including: Esta Lichtenstein, Jess Kent, Barbara Miller, Morissa Sher Wiser, Steffi Aronson Karp, Terri Swartz Russell, Sally Bock\" width=\"150\" height=\"113\" /></a>\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\">LimmudBoston 2011 Planners, including: Esta Lichtenstein, Jess Kent, Barbara Miller, Morissa Sher Wiser, Steffi Aronson Karp, Terri Swartz Russell, Sally Bock</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Who We Are','','inherit','closed','closed','','53-revision-v1','','','2017-05-26 12:53:41','2017-05-26 17:53:41','',53,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/53-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(114,3,'2017-05-26 12:53:59','2017-05-26 17:53:59','<h1>Who We Are</h1>\r\n<div class=\"post-entry\">\r\n<div id=\"attachment_2972\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\">\r\n\r\n<a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/2016-12-04-LimmudBoston-Board.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-0\" data-imagelightbox=\"0\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-2972\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/2016-12-04-LimmudBoston-Board-150x116.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/2016-12-04-LimmudBoston-Board-150x116.jpg 150w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/2016-12-04-LimmudBoston-Board-300x232.jpg 300w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/2016-12-04-LimmudBoston-Board-768x593.jpg 768w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/2016-12-04-LimmudBoston-Board-1024x791.jpg 1024w\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"116\" /></a>\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Board: Eric Karp, Alan Teperow (Chair), Terri Swartz Russell, Sean Wald, Marcia Plumb, Emma Stitcher, Steffi Aronson Karp, Wendy Liebow, Julie Wolkoff, Naomi Gurt Lind <em>Photo: Meri Bond</em></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLimmudBoston is a volunteer-driven, independent, pan-denominational organization dedicated to the creation of engaging opportunities to experience and celebrate Jewish learning and culture.\r\n\r\nVolunteer + Participate = <a title=\"Volunticipate\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/volunticipate/\">Volunticipate</a>! <a title=\"Volunticipate\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/volunticipate/\">Click here to join a team now</a>.\r\n\r\nLike Limmud conferences everywhere, LimmudBoston runs on volunteer power. Our volunteer teams include:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Program  Shabbat; Chavruta; Site &amp; Signage; Volunteer Coordination; Program Book; Music &amp; Performance; PR &amp; Outreach; Food; Technology</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nLimmudBoston is part of Limmud International, and represents one of more than 80 independent worldwide Limmud conferences. We follow <a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/about/values-and-principles-of-limmud-international/\">Limmud International Values &amp; Principles</a>.\r\n<h2>Who We Are</h2>\r\n<div class=\"clear\">\r\n<h3><a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Steffi-e1430062700303.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-1\" data-imagelightbox=\"1\"><img class=\"clear wp-image-2030 size-thumbnail alignleft\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Steffi-e1430062700303-130x150.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 130px) 100vw, 130px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Steffi-e1430062700303-130x150.jpg 130w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Steffi-e1430062700303-261x300.jpg 261w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Steffi-e1430062700303.jpg 482w\" alt=\"Steffi Aronson Karp\" width=\"130\" height=\"150\" /></a>Steffi Aronson Karp, President</h3>\r\nLimmudBoston is run from the home of Steffi Aronson Karp, founder of LimmudBoston, who has been a Jewish conference junkie since her high school days in NEFTY, NFTY and SMARTY on Boston’s North Shore. In 2008, after attending her first Limmud in Atlanta, GA, she began creating LimmudBoston.  Steffi has participated in Limmud conferences in the UK, Philadelphia, New York and Baltimore, Miami, New Orleans and Toronto. In 2013, Steffi received the Klal Yisrael Award from the Synagogue Council of Massachusetts, as recognition for uniting area Jewish communities through LimmudBoston.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clear\">\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-41 size-thumbnail\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/concert_steffi_terri-e1430062072891-101x150.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 101px) 100vw, 101px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/concert_steffi_terri-e1430062072891-101x150.jpg 101w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/concert_steffi_terri-e1430062072891-202x300.jpg 202w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/concert_steffi_terri-e1430062072891-688x1024.jpg 688w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/concert_steffi_terri-e1430062072891.jpg 712w\" alt=\"Terri Swartz Russell\" width=\"101\" height=\"150\" />Terri Swartz Russell, LimmudBoston Board</h3>\r\nTerri Swartz Russell is the Family Educator at Temple Emanuel in Newton. She is an active member of Temple Emunah, Lexington, where she serves as co-chair of its Adult Education committee. Terri was the first to volunteer for LimmudBoston, was co-chair of the conference from 2011-2013, and currently serves as the Chair of the LimmudBoston Board.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clear\">\r\n<h3><img class=\"clear alignleft wp-image-1657 size-thumbnail\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/standing_in_lobby-e1430061616439-125x150.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 125px) 100vw, 125px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/standing_in_lobby-e1430061616439-125x150.jpg 125w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/standing_in_lobby-e1430061616439-251x300.jpg 251w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/standing_in_lobby-e1430061616439.jpg 254w\" alt=\"Jeri Robins\" width=\"125\" height=\"150\" />Jeri Robins, Music Team Leader</h3>\r\nCantor Robins has led the Music Team for LimmudBoston for several years. She currently serves Temple Beth Shalom of the North Shore in Peabody, Massachusetts in the dual role of Cantor and Director of Education.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clear\">\r\n<h3>Julie Wolkoff, Vice Chair<img class=\"clear alignleft wp-image-1600 size-thumbnail\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Volunteering-signs-e1430061422869-137x150.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 137px) 100vw, 137px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Volunteering-signs-e1430061422869-137x150.jpg 137w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Volunteering-signs-e1430061422869-273x300.jpg 273w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Volunteering-signs-e1430061422869.jpg 338w\" alt=\"Julie Wolkoff\" width=\"137\" height=\"150\" /></h3>\r\nRabbi Julie Wolkoff, D.Min. was ordained from HUC-JIR in 1982. She received her Doctor of Ministry degree from HUC-JIR in 1996. She is a chaplain with Care Alternatives Hospice in Marlborough, MA.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h3>Wendy Liebow</h3>\r\nWendy Liebow has many years of program experience at Temple Isaiah in Lexington, where she served two terms as VP of Programming and many more co-chairing various committees.    She lives in Lexington with her husband, Scott Burson.\r\n<h3>Barbara Posnick</h3>\r\nBarbara Posnick, of Wayland, served as Program Book editor for LimmudBoston 2012.  This year she is working with Wendy Liebow as Co-Chair of the Program Team.\r\n<h3>Barbara Miller</h3>\r\nBarbara Miller wrote to LimmudBoston in 2009 to say that she’s “in.” Put her to work. And we’ve done just that. Barbara has led the Site Team, working closely with every group in order to make sure that the building fits the needs of LimmudBoston.\r\n<h3>EJ Cohen-Music Team</h3>\r\nEJ Cohen brings years of experience with Limmud UK to the new world version, LimmudBoston.  She has spent 30+ years combining expertise from the worlds of Deaf and Jewish education.\r\n<h3>Maureen Mintz-Food Team</h3>\r\nMaureen Mintz  It wouldn’t be a Jewish conference without food, and lots of it. Maureen Mintz and her Food Team communicate with our kosher caterers, to bring yummy lunch to LimmudBoston participants. The food team also arranges for lots of snacks throughout the conference day.\r\n<h3>Emma Stitcher-Signage Queen</h3>\r\nLimmudBoston is lucky to have Emma Stitcher, our Signage expert. Emma and her family attended many Limmuds when they lived in the UK. In fact, the Stitcher daughters celebrated their b’not mitvah at Limmud. Emma also serves as our best on-site advisor for WWLD–What would Limmud do?!\r\n<div id=\"attachment_202\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\">\r\n\r\n<a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/whoWeAre_steffiTerri.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-2\" data-imagelightbox=\"2\"><img class=\" wp-image-202\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/whoWeAre_steffiTerri.jpg\" alt=\"Steffi Aronson Karp and Terri Swartz Russell\" width=\"170\" height=\"113\" /></a>\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Steffi Aronson Karp and Terri Swartz Russell</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"attachment_201\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\">\r\n\r\n<a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/whoWeAre_2012Team.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-3\" data-imagelightbox=\"3\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-201\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/whoWeAre_2012Team.jpg\" alt=\" Terri Swartz Russell with LimmudBoston 2012 Program Team leaders, Barbara Posnick (left) and Wendy Liebow (right)\" width=\"150\" height=\"113\" /></a>\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Terri Swartz Russell with LimmudBoston 2012 Program Team leaders, Barbara Posnick (left) and Wendy Liebow (right)</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"attachment_200\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\">\r\n\r\n<a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/whoWeAre_2011Team.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-4\" data-imagelightbox=\"4\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-200\" src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/whoWeAre_2011Team.jpg\" alt=\"LimmudBoston 2011 Planners, including: Esta Lichtenstein, Jess Kent, Barbara Miller, Morissa Sher Wiser, Steffi Aronson Karp, Terri Swartz Russell, Sally Bock\" width=\"150\" height=\"113\" /></a>\r\n<p class=\"wp-caption-text\">LimmudBoston 2011 Planners, including: Esta Lichtenstein, Jess Kent, Barbara Miller, Morissa Sher Wiser, Steffi Aronson Karp, Terri Swartz Russell, Sally Bock</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Who We Are','','inherit','closed','closed','','53-revision-v1','','','2017-05-26 12:53:59','2017-05-26 17:53:59','',53,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/53-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(115,3,'2017-05-26 12:56:37','2017-05-26 17:56:37','<h1>LimmudBoston Newsletters</h1>\r\n<div class=\"post-entry\">\r\n\r\nStay up to date with the latest LimmudBoston Newsletter.\r\n\r\nJoin the LimmudBoston Mailing List <a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/about/contact-us/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<strong>Newsletter Archive</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hosted.verticalresponse.com/682162/7d55d428bd/1376008003/3fbba437dc/\">2017-05-26</a> - Join Our Advisory Team and Shavuot\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hosted.verticalresponse.com/682162/aa0a865d62/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">November 25, 2016</a> – One Week Countdown\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hosted.verticalresponse.com/682162/8ad52df523/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">November 23, 2016</a> – Silent Auction Now Open\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hosted.verticalresponse.com/682162/d9ed10f9da/1376008003/865feb1551/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">November 18, 2018</a>: Two Week Countdown\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hosted.verticalresponse.com/682162/fa8f2f8744/1376008003/865feb1551/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">November 14, 2016</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://hosted.verticalrespo