://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Age-diversity-300x200.jpg 300w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Age-diversity-150x100.jpg 150w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Age-diversity.jpg 800w\" alt=\"Two volunticipants: an old woman and a young man\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a>©Meri Bond</p>\n<p><strong>Anyone may offer to present a session! </strong>Just like the 80+ Limmud conferences held around the world, the LimmudBoston program team reviews session proposals from anyone with a passion to present a Jewish topic. Presenters also attend LimmudBoston as learners.</p>\n<p><strong>Volunteers make LimmudBoston! </strong>Nearly everyone pitches in by both paying to attend the conference, and or volunteering to help with a planning team, or by choosing a task on conference day.</p>\n<h4><em>No matter where you are on the spectrum of Jewish living, there is more to learn and more to do. As we learn from Pirke Avot, “Turn it and turn it for everything is in it, and through it you will perceive clearly.”</em> — Pirkei Avot, Chapters of the Sages. 5:26</h4>\n<h2>Shabbat: The REST of LimmudBoston</h2>\n<p>The entire community can be a weekend of learning when area congregations engage LimmudBoston presenters for Shabbat. We will list your congregation as a LimmudBoston Shabbat opportunity if your congregation:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your congregation wants to hire one of the LimmudBoston presenters coming for our Sunday conference; or</li>\n<li>Your Congregation already has a Shabbat speaker who will inspire Jewish learning\n<ul>\n<li><a title=\"Shabbat: The REST of Limmud\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/shabbat/\">LimmudBoston Shabbat experience programs</a> in area synagogues. LimmudBoston presenters serve as visiting scholars throughout the area. Learn more on our Shabbat Experience page.  Your Shabbat community can be one of a select group of Boston area synagogues to host a special Shabbat learning opportunity in conjunction with our upcoming LimmudBoston conference.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Everyone is welcome at LimmudBoston</h2>\n<p>LimmudBoston offers lots of points of view. LimmudBoston events are for beginners and scholars; the young and the young-at-heart. The Limmud flavor includes diversity of presenters, topics, style, age, participation, gender participation and traditions.</p>\n<p>For more information on attending as a teenager, see <a title=\"Teens at LimmudBoston\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2014/teens-at-limmudboston/\">this page</a>.</p>\n<h2>Camp Limmud</h2>\n<p><a title=\"\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kids_from_back.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-2\" data-imagelightbox=\"2\"><img src=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kids_from_back-200x300.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" srcset=\"https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kids_from_back-200x300.jpg 200w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kids_from_back-100x150.jpg 100w, https://limmudboston.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kids_from_back.jpg 533w\" alt=\"Kids gathered around a table\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<p>©2014 Meri Bond</p>\n<p>The <a title=\"Camp Limmud\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/conference-2014/camp-limmud/\">Camp Limmud program </a>offers child care and programming for children ages 3-14. Presenters from LimmudBoston have also presented for the Camp Limmud kids. Camp Limmud participation is by reservation only.</p>\n<h3>Want to know more?</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a title=\"Testimonials\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/about/testimonials/\">Testimonials</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Values and Principles of Limmud International\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/about/values-and-principles-of-limmud-international/\">Values and Principles</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"LimmudBoston in the News\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/about/limmudboston-in-the-news/\">LimmudBoston in the News</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://limmudboston.org/about/who-we-are/\">Our Board</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Ready to get involved?</h3>\n<p><a title=\"Volunticipate\" href=\"https://limmudboston.org/volunticipate/\">Click here to volunteer</a> or send an email to: <a href=\"mailto:info@limmudboston.org\">info@Limmudboston.org</a></p>\n','About Us','','inherit','closed','closed','','109-revision-v1','','','2017-06-02 23:33:28','2017-06-03 04:33:28','',109,'http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/109-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(228,6,'2017-06-02 23:45:02','2017-06-03 04:45:02','<h1>\n		Inspirational! Educational! Just Sensational!\n	</h1>\n	<style>\n.hp-circle-container {\n    background: orange;\n    border: 3px solid yellow;\n    border-radius: 50%;\n    margin: 0 auto;\n    height: 200px;\n    width: 200px;\n    text-align: center;\n    vertical-align: middle;\n}\n.hp-circle-container span.text {\n    padding-top: .5rem;\n    color: red;\n}\n</style>\n        Volunteer\n				<a href=\"#\" target=\"_self\" itemprop=\"url\">\n				<img src=\"http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/uploads/2017/05/conference-button-VOLUNTEER--285x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" itemprop=\"image\"  />\n				</a>\n	<h3><a href=\"#\" target=\"_self\">Volunticipate</a></h3>		\n			<p><strong>Program Team / Advisory Team / Day-of Choices / Other</strong></p>\n				<a href=\"#\" target=\"_self\" itemprop=\"url\">\n				<img src=\"http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/uploads/2017/05/Home-Page-conference-button-register--300x297.jpg\" alt=\"\" itemprop=\"image\"  />\n				</a>\n	<h3><a href=\"#\" target=\"_self\">Conference 2017</a></h3>		\n			<p><strong>Session Proposal Form / Conference Info &amp; Schedule / Camp Limmud</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Shabbat: the REST of Limmud</strong></p>\n				<a href=\"#\" target=\"_self\" itemprop=\"url\">\n				<img src=\"http://limmudboston.48in48sites.org/uploads/2017/05/conference-button-SUPPORT-1-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" itemprop=\"image\"  />\n				</a>\n	<h3><a href=\"#\" target=\"_self\">Support</a></