th=\"225\" height=\"225\" /></p>\n<p>Please click on this Donate button:</p>\n<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\" target=\"_top\"><input alt=\"PayPal - The safer, easier way to pay online!\" name=\"submit\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donateCC_LG.gif\" type=\"image\" /></p>\n</form>\n<p>Your LimmudBoston donation helps us continue the work which inspires and unites New England’s many Jewish communities, and helps us continue the core practice of Limmud International, that all who wish to learn can be included, regardless of financial circumstances.</p>\n<p>LimmudBoston, Inc. is a 501(c)3 tax exempt organization. Contributions are tax deductible to the extent allowed by law as long as LimmudBoston, Inc. provided no goods or services in exchange for your contribution.</p>\n<p>Donations received before November 15 will be acknowledged in the annual LimmudBoston conference program book given to every conference attendee.</p>\n<p>Please consider the following amounts, or choose an amount that fits your wallet:</p>\n<p><strong>Pillars of Learning</strong>, $500 or more, helps to fund a presenter; receives 4 admissions;</p>\n<p><strong>Prophets</strong>, $360-499, receive conference admission for four;</p>\n<p><strong>Scholars</strong>, $180-359, receive conference admission for two;</p>\n<p><strong>Learners</strong>, $118-179, receive conference admission for one;</p>\n<p><strong>Well-Wishers</strong>, $72 &amp; above, will be listed in the LimmudBoston Program Book.</p>\n<p>Here is another opportunity to click on the DONATE button:</p>\n<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\" target=\"_top\"><input alt=\"PayPal - The safer, easier way to pay online!\" name=\"submit\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donateCC_LG.gif\" type=\"image\" /></p>\n</form>\n<p>If you prefer, you can send a check by mail. Please make your check payable to LimmudBoston with “LimmudBoston” in